===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A [[location]] or place.
# A particular moment in an [[event]] or occurrence.
#:''At this point in the meeting, I'd like to propose a new item for the agenda.''
# The sharp [[tip]] of an [[object]].
# (''arithmetic'') A [[decimal point]] (''used when reading decimal fractions aloud'').
#:''10.5'' ("ten point five"; = ten and a half)
# An opinion which adds (or supposedly adds) to the [[discussion]].
# A unit of measure of [[success]] or [[failure]] in a [[game]] or [[competition]].
#:''The one with the most points will win the game''
#:''Germany awarded Greece the maximum 12 points in the Eurovision Song Contest.''
# The [[color]]/[[colour]] on the [[extremities]] of an [[animal]] (typically [[dark]]er or [[rich]]er) than the rest of the [[coat]]).
#:''The point color of that cat was a deep, rich sable.'' 
#a [[device]] by which [[train]]s [[change]] [[track]]s
# {{Icehockey}} The [[stastistical]] combination of [[goal]]s and [[assist]]s.
#:''The player had one goal and two assists for three points in that game.''
# {{cricket}} a [[fielding]] [[position]] [[square]] of the [[wicket]] on the [[off side]], between [[gully]] and [[cover]].

